# NurseNest Production Governance

- Keep edits surgical. Do not rewrite unrelated files.
- No schema, migration, or response-shape changes unless explicitly requested.
- Preserve learner route behavior: Lessons, Flashcards, Questions, CAT, dashboard, paywall, and entitlements must keep working.
- Admin and staff access stay server-enforced. DB role state is the source of truth; do not trust JWT alone.
- Do not invent parallel auth systems or move security-sensitive logic client-side.
- Preserve locale, i18n, SEO, sitemap, robots, and canonical behavior.
- Header, nav, and footer changes must not clip labels, wrap mid-label, or hide critical controls.
- Do not reintroduce the arch graphic.
- Do not add heavy libraries, touch env/secrets, or silently change app-wide copy unless explicitly asked.
- After auth, dashboard, nav, lesson, or paywall edits, run focused validation and report what you verified.
